  scenario="It is Saturday afternoon. A restaurant owner in East Oxford is refurbishing his premises — the interior designer has specified a full package of bespoke metalwork for the fit-out: a 12-metre run of industrial-style bar railings in blackened mild steel with brass cap rail, four wall-mounted shelving units fabricated from 20mm square bar with welded mesh shelves, a steel-framed entrance door with Crittall-style glazing bars, and external seating barriers in matching blackened steel with laser-cut branding panels. He WhatsApps three fabrication workshops with photos of the designer's mood board: 'Hi — refurbing our restaurant and need a full metalwork package. Bar railings, shelving, entrance door, and external barriers. All in a blackened industrial style. Designer has drawings but we need a fabricator who can interpret and deliver the whole thing. Fit-out starts in 8 weeks. Can you handle all of it?' Without AI WhatsApp, you see the message Sunday. One workshop replied Saturday evening with relevant restaurant metalwork examples. With AI WhatsApp, the response arrives within seconds, asks about access for delivery, whether the blackened finish is wax or lacquer, and requests the designer's drawings. He sends the mood board spread. Sunday you open the lead: restaurant fit-out, East Oxford, full metalwork package, bar rail/shelving/door/barriers, blackened mild steel with brass, designer drawings available, 8-week start. You call Monday at 9am."
